                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>New York</placeName>\n                <date>March 15<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi>, 1860</date>.</p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">My Dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">I have the pleasure of<lb/> acknowledging the receipt of your favor\n                of<lb/> the <date>13<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> Ins. enclosing check for $41.50<lb/>\n                <add>?</add> the hands of <persName>Mr Allen</persName>, you<lb/> received I suppose\n                a List from<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr<lb/> Isaacs</persName>. <add>?</add> his return of money<lb/> collected\n                in the Messengers office amounting<lb/> to $340.20 also $240.60 <del>recd</del>\n                recd<lb/> from sh<add>?</add> I think this about<lb/> closes our collections</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">You will oblige me by<lb/> sending on your full Bill now<lb/> for\n                advertising, the last Bill was only up<lb/> to a certain date &amp; is now increased\n                by<lb/> recent advertisement. Please let<lb/> me have to date &amp; I will remit\n                you<lb/> my check for the amount.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">With best respects I remain<lb/> yours truly</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(6)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">Henry I Hart</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ww77k5m/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
